Centre for the Analysis of Motion, Entertainment Research and Applications (CAMERA), University of Bath

EmoGen Tool is provided as a set of source code files, a compilation script installing the tool itself and supporting third-party libraries (*) 
and a configuration script to run the tool.

The supporting assets are all the additional data files supplied with the tool and required to run it. These include, but are not limited to, 3D mesh files (e.g. .obj, textures etc), binary and text files in /data/.

The tool may be used strictly for non-commercial purposes (e.g. academic research) only. 
The supporting assets may only be used in conjuction with the tool and not for any other purpose, commercial or otherwise.

Any publication involving the use of the tool must cite us as its developers.

The source code and the supporting assets cannot be redistributed in any form.

